data.content:
Yes — MSTest v3.4+ supports **value tuples** with `DynamicData`, giving you compile-time type safety:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**What changed:**
- `IEnumerable<object[]>` → `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` — the compiler now enforces that each row has the correct types and arity
- Square brackets `[…]` → parentheses `(…)` for each row (tuples instead of arrays)

The test method signature stays the same. MSTest automatically destructures the tuple into the method parameters.
